<i>♪ Talespin ♪</i>

01:19.083 --> 01:20.834
[gunfire]

01:31.458 --> 01:32.625
[grunts]

01:55.792 --> 01:59.166
Greetings and salivations, fellow aviator.

01:59.250 --> 02:04.959
It is I, that panic-provoking pirate,
Don Karnage.

02:05.041 --> 02:08.458
Mayday, mayday, this is flight 127.

02:12.333 --> 02:14.500
Tsk, tsk, tsk, such manners.

02:14.583 --> 02:17.834
Shere Khan owns this plane,
you slimy thief.

02:17.959 --> 02:19.333
[all chattering]

02:19.458 --> 02:20.542
[gulps]

02:20.625 --> 02:22.792
The box, if you please.

02:34.166 --> 02:36.959
What blows up must come down.

02:37.041 --> 02:40.291
Men, back to the <i>Iron Vulture!</i>

02:55.458 --> 03:00.000
At last, the key to my future. [laughs]

03:00.083 --> 03:01.917
Riches, my men.

03:02.000 --> 03:06.750
Riches beyond your limited,
insignificant dreams.

03:06.834 --> 03:09.375
But not beyond mine. [laughs]

03:09.458 --> 03:12.417
For soon, I, Don Karnage,

03:12.500 --> 03:15.583
shall be the wealthiest man in the world!

03:16.709 --> 03:17.625
[grunts]

03:17.709 --> 03:20.333
For me? Aw, you shouldn't have.

03:20.959 --> 03:24.291
Well, it was nothing, really...
Stop that boy!

03:28.750 --> 03:31.583
Don't just stand there,
the captain needs your help.

03:32.375 --> 03:33.583
[grunts]

03:39.458 --> 03:41.917
[groans] Get him, you idiots!

03:53.542 --> 03:55.125
Whoops!

03:56.959 --> 04:02.041
Well, my reckless reptile,
perhaps it is none of my business,

04:02.125 --> 04:06.500
but, uh, you've gotten yourself
in a tiny piccolo. Yes, no?

04:06.583 --> 04:10.375
You know, you're right.
It is none of your business.

04:12.917 --> 04:15.083
No! My treasure.

04:17.125 --> 04:20.041
After him! After him!

04:33.834 --> 04:35.125
[bird caws]

04:35.208 --> 04:37.208
Breaker, breaker. Come in, Louie.

04:40.291 --> 04:42.959
Hey, has the party started yet?

04:43.208 --> 04:44.208
What was that?

04:44.291 --> 04:45.458
[grunts]

04:46.792 --> 04:48.792
Wa-hoo!

04:48.875 --> 04:50.750
[laughing]

04:54.458 --> 04:56.667
[people laughing]

05:06.041 --> 05:10.125
Oh, man, Baloo, sometimes running
this place is like working in a zoo.

05:10.208 --> 05:15.750
Hey, Louie, you got to learn
my secret to relaxation.

05:15.834 --> 05:18.291
Oh, and what's that, cuz?

05:19.041 --> 05:20.500
[music plays]

05:20.583 --> 05:23.083
Oh, yeah, man.

05:25.709 --> 05:27.166
Hey-hey.

05:27.250 --> 05:29.333
<i>♪ When life down here's a funny cloud ♪</i>

05:29.417 --> 05:31.291
<i>♪ I take off for the air ♪</i>

05:31.375 --> 05:34.250
<i>♪ I soar above the madding crowd ♪</i>

05:34.333 --> 05:36.166
<i>♪ Without a single care ♪</i>

05:36.250 --> 05:38.291
<i>♪ And I'm not one to stick around ♪</i>

05:38.375 --> 05:40.583
<i>♪ When problems start to brew ♪</i>

05:40.667 --> 05:42.625
<i>♪ So, see you later, navigator ♪</i>

05:42.709 --> 05:44.583
<i>♪ I know just what to do ♪</i>

05:44.667 --> 05:46.000
<i>♪ I'm gone ♪</i>

05:46.083 --> 05:47.041
<i>♪ He's gonna fly ♪</i>

05:47.125 --> 05:48.291
<i>♪ I am gone ♪</i>

05:48.375 --> 05:49.291
<i>♪ Adios, bye-bye ♪</i>

05:49.375 --> 05:52.291
<i>♪ Don't trouble me with troubles, man</i>
<i>I'm gone ♪</i>

05:52.375 --> 05:54.542
<i>-♪ Oh, he's gone ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I am gone ♪</i>

05:54.625 --> 05:57.125
<i>-♪ Wait a minute ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I'm gone ♪</i>

05:57.208 --> 05:58.208
<i>♪ The sky's the limit ♪</i>

05:58.291 --> 06:00.750
<i>♪ I love to be above it all I'm gone ♪</i>

06:00.834 --> 06:03.208
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, he's gone, he's gone ♪</i>

06:03.291 --> 06:04.417
<i>♪ Ho-ho, yeah ♪</i>

06:04.500 --> 06:06.959
<i>-♪ He's gone ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Lay it on me, Jack ♪</i>

06:07.041 --> 06:08.417
<i>♪ Don't trouble him ♪</i>

06:08.500 --> 06:09.542
<i>♪ With trouble, man He's gone ♪</i>

06:09.625 --> 06:10.834
<i>♪ Ba doo da, boo de bom ♪</i>

06:10.917 --> 06:11.875
<i>♪ He's gone ♪</i>

06:11.959 --> 06:13.291
<i>♪ Check the wind, babe ♪</i>

06:13.375 --> 06:14.250
<i>♪ He's gone ♪</i>

06:14.333 --> 06:15.417
<i>♪ Holy cha-cha ♪</i>

06:15.500 --> 06:17.667
<i>♪ He loves to be above it all ♪</i>

06:17.750 --> 06:19.291
<i>- ♪ He's gone ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ I'm gone ♪</i>

06:21.625 --> 06:22.917
[groans]

06:23.875 --> 06:27.542
Well, well. What have we here?

06:27.625 --> 06:30.333
Come here, you half-pint hitchhiker.

06:32.041 --> 06:35.166
Aw, cut the kid some slack, Jack.

06:35.250 --> 06:38.625
-Yeah, listen to the fat lady.
-Lady?

06:38.709 --> 06:40.375
-Whatever.
-[stammering]

06:40.458 --> 06:42.917
Didn't know he was a pal of yours, Baloo.

06:43.000 --> 06:44.834
No hard feelings, OK.

06:45.959 --> 06:47.583
Nice kid.

06:49.125 --> 06:52.375
That was quite an entrance,
little britches.

06:52.458 --> 06:55.542
-Hey, you're a pilot!
-Last I checked.

06:55.625 --> 07:00.125
-Are you good?
-[chuckles] The best, kid. <i>Numero uno.</i>

07:00.208 --> 07:02.917
Uh... I'm going to be a pilot someday.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.750
Yeah. Bet you will be, too.

07:05.834 --> 07:09.917
-Hey, nice luggage.
-Hands off, it's mine!

07:10.000 --> 07:13.000
Easy, kid. I'm just admiring.

07:13.083 --> 07:15.750
Well, see you in the funny papers.

07:16.166 --> 07:17.709
Look, I didn't...

07:18.291 --> 07:19.959
Oh, forget it.

07:20.041 --> 07:21.917
[banging]

07:22.000 --> 07:25.792
I am sorry to fracture the festivities...

07:28.709 --> 07:30.542
but I have a brief announcement.

07:32.208 --> 07:35.458
Get out of my place, Karnage!

07:35.542 --> 07:37.667
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

07:37.959 --> 07:41.583
Now, I am looking for a boy

07:41.667 --> 07:44.208
who has stolen something from me.

07:44.291 --> 07:48.125
Hand him over and I will leave peacefully.

07:48.208 --> 07:50.000
If not...

07:50.083 --> 07:51.250
[gunshot]

07:58.417 --> 08:01.166
<i>♪ Do ba do be do ba de do ♪</i>

08:04.000 --> 08:06.208
Miss me, baby?

08:11.917 --> 08:14.250
That a girl. Talk to me.

08:14.333 --> 08:17.500
You have made Don Karnage,

08:17.583 --> 08:20.542
which is me, very unhappy.

08:20.625 --> 08:23.333
Boys, tear the place asunder!

08:23.417 --> 08:26.375
Don't bother. I was just on my way out.

08:26.458 --> 08:27.792
Get him!

08:28.250 --> 08:30.417
[all yelling]

08:33.708 --> 08:36.792
It's been fun, guys,
but I got to be going.

08:36.875 --> 08:38.207
Yahoo!

08:56.250 --> 08:59.917
Oh, baby, that's my girl. [hums]

09:00.000 --> 09:02.083
[knocking on window]

09:02.166 --> 09:03.250
Hello?

09:03.333 --> 09:06.166
Oh, hiya, kid. You need a lift?

09:11.125 --> 09:12.291
Mm-hmm!

09:12.375 --> 09:16.917
OK by me, though it's comfier inside.

09:18.000 --> 09:21.291
[Kit] Oh, what a great plane.

09:21.375 --> 09:25.166
-A Conwing L-16, right?
-Good eye, kid.

09:25.250 --> 09:29.458
I call her the <i>Sea Duck, </i> my best friend.

09:29.542 --> 09:31.375
Customized her myself.

09:31.458 --> 09:35.458
Yeah, like those engines,
Superfly 100s, right?

09:35.542 --> 09:40.458
He-- Hey, you're all right, kid.
What do they call you?

09:40.542 --> 09:46.041
-Kit. Kit Cloudkicker.
-Glad to meet you, Kit.

09:48.291 --> 09:50.083
I'm gonna buy a plane one day.

09:50.166 --> 09:52.583
I hope your folks are rich.

09:52.667 --> 09:55.041
I don't have any folks,

09:55.125 --> 09:58.792
but I'm gonna be rich! And real soon, too.

09:58.875 --> 10:02.959
Well, if you're gonna get a plane,
you better know how to fly it.

10:04.625 --> 10:06.750
Me? Really?

10:06.834 --> 10:10.583
-[chuckles] Knock yourself out.
-Wow!

10:12.750 --> 10:17.625
[Baloo] Hey, relax, little britches.
Just hold her steady.

10:17.917 --> 10:19.917
That's it.

10:20.542 --> 10:23.834
Say, you're a dandy.

10:23.917 --> 10:27.458
Yeah, but I can't get my license
for five more years.

10:27.542 --> 10:30.500
[Baloo]
But when you do, you'll be a regular ace.

10:30.583 --> 10:33.041
-[gunfire]
-What was that?

10:33.375 --> 10:37.208
Well, back on the corner where I hang out,
we call that "pirates."

10:44.542 --> 10:45.959
[Don Karnage] Do what you want
to the plane,

10:46.041 --> 10:48.667
but I want the boy untouched,

10:48.750 --> 10:53.166
so I can tear him to little
bite-sized pieces!

10:59.166 --> 11:03.792
What are they after me for?
I don't have anything they want.

11:03.875 --> 11:05.959
Not necessarily.

11:16.709 --> 11:18.250
Follow me!

11:22.542 --> 11:24.333
[Kit] Baloo!

11:25.709 --> 11:29.875
Boy, they're tougher to shake
than ticks on a dog.

11:30.917 --> 11:34.250
We aren't gonna make it! Pull up! Pull up!

11:34.333 --> 11:38.583
Now just hold on.
Old Baloo's not out of tricks yet.

11:38.667 --> 11:41.083
[all yelling]

11:44.333 --> 11:47.750
You... No one can fly like that!

11:47.834 --> 11:50.875
Great pilot. Great plane.

11:50.959 --> 11:53.458
I'll say. So, what's next?

11:53.542 --> 11:55.125
[Baloo] A quick exit.

11:55.208 --> 11:57.667
But you can fly rings around them.

11:57.750 --> 12:00.333
Don't have to.
That's Cape Suzette up ahead.

12:01.333 --> 12:03.291
[Kit] But we'll never make it in time.

12:03.375 --> 12:05.291
[Baloo] Those puffs of smoke say we will.

12:05.375 --> 12:06.625
Huh?

12:07.417 --> 12:10.500
No, the Cape Suzette cannons!

12:13.166 --> 12:17.583
Ooh! They make me so angry!
Retreat. Retreat!

12:17.667 --> 12:21.000
But soon I will have the last ha-ha,

12:21.083 --> 12:24.125
after I get the boy and the box.

12:27.000 --> 12:30.917
Those bozos can never
seem to get past the cliff guns.

12:31.000 --> 12:34.208
[laughs] Drives them crazy.

12:49.875 --> 12:53.917
[Baloo] Cape Suzette, kiddo.
What do you think?

12:54.000 --> 12:55.250
Wow!

13:22.834 --> 13:26.125
Ahh, it's good to be back.

13:30.875 --> 13:33.959
Hey, hey, the Sox won the series.

13:34.083 --> 13:38.417
[laughs] That paper is two months old,
just like these unpaid bills.

13:38.500 --> 13:43.500
That's all detail stuff, kid.
Me, I'm a big picture kind of guy.

13:43.583 --> 13:47.250
-No way to run an airline.
-Look, I only work

13:47.333 --> 13:52.291
when I have to, no more.
Flying is what life's all about.

13:52.375 --> 13:56.250
In fact, I've been thinking
of adding a navigator.

13:56.333 --> 13:59.417
-Interested?
-Me? Oh, no way.

13:59.500 --> 14:01.208
I got to get back to Louie's place.

14:01.291 --> 14:05.709
-Uh, didn't we just leave there?
-Yeah, and I want to go back, OK.

14:05.792 --> 14:09.083
This tough guy routine
work on all your friends?

14:09.166 --> 14:14.583
-I... don't have any friends.
-Look, sorry, Kit.

14:14.667 --> 14:17.792
But I'm not due back at Louie's
for a few weeks.

14:18.583 --> 14:22.125
-[knocking on door]
-But I have to go now.

14:22.208 --> 14:25.375
-[man] Mr. Baloo?
-The one and only.

14:25.458 --> 14:30.542
I'm from the Cape Suzette National Bank
about your plane.

14:30.625 --> 14:33.542
[Baloo] Yeah, ain't she a beauty?

14:33.625 --> 14:37.291
You, sir, are delinquent
on your last six payments

14:37.375 --> 14:40.208
and unless funds totaling $3,000

14:40.291 --> 14:45.083
are deposited in our fiduciary institution
by 9:00 a.m., tomorrow,

14:45.166 --> 14:48.834
we will be forced to foreclose
on your aircraft loan.

14:48.917 --> 14:52.959
You're gonna take my plane?
You can't. That's my baby!

14:53.041 --> 14:55.792
We have sent numerous notices.

14:56.375 --> 14:58.000
Just like these unpaid bills.

14:58.083 --> 15:00.667
I... I thought those
were sweepstakes giveaways.

15:00.750 --> 15:02.333
Good day.

15:03.250 --> 15:08.166
But 3,000 smackers?
No! What am I going to do?

15:08.250 --> 15:09.709
What am I going to do?

15:09.792 --> 15:13.834
-Couldn't you take a job, or something?
-A job?

15:14.000 --> 15:18.041
Kit, you're a genius, with a capital J.

15:18.125 --> 15:22.041
[laughs] I'll just find a job here
on the old job board.

15:22.125 --> 15:27.625
-Can you really make $3,000 this fast?
-Yeah, if the job's nasty enough.

15:27.709 --> 15:29.792
Ah-ha, a zoo delivery!

15:29.875 --> 15:33.750
Wait. What exactly are we delivering?

15:33.834 --> 15:38.291
Well, they're sort of, uh, big and mean,

15:38.542 --> 15:42.709
and, and, and ugly, and smelly.

15:42.792 --> 15:45.875
Oh, no! Not gorilla birds!

15:53.291 --> 15:55.125
See? Nothing to it.

15:55.208 --> 15:58.834
-Yeah, right.
-It's a piece of cake.

15:58.917 --> 16:02.083
Get them out of here!
They're eating my plane!

16:02.166 --> 16:04.667
[yelling]

16:06.917 --> 16:09.083
Whew, close one.

16:09.166 --> 16:12.792
-Hey, whose side are you on?
-Sorry!

16:12.875 --> 16:16.125
Lock them up in the back.
Is that too much to ask?

16:16.208 --> 16:20.166
Hey, wait, you're the one who said,
"This is gonna be a piece of cake."

16:20.875 --> 16:23.709
[Baloo]
It looks like we're in for some icing.

16:27.083 --> 16:29.166
[Don Karnage] Get them, my men. Get them!

16:29.250 --> 16:30.750
[Baloo] Pirates again?

16:30.834 --> 16:34.917
-What could these guys possibly want?
-Don't look at me.

16:38.750 --> 16:40.959
Hang on, little britches.

17:12.875 --> 17:16.791
[laughing] Hey, my flying is A-plus.

17:16.875 --> 17:18.125
Whoa!

17:18.208 --> 17:21.290
[Baloo and Kit yelling]

17:34.834 --> 17:38.041
Yeah, but your landings are C-minus.

17:38.125 --> 17:42.458
[Don Karnage] Curses and more curses!
They are down there somewhere.

17:42.542 --> 17:46.625
-Find the boy, got it?
-[man] Yeah, we got it.

17:49.834 --> 17:52.417
I'm sorry, baby. You OK?

17:52.500 --> 17:54.667
Phew. I think we lost them.

17:54.750 --> 17:57.542
Maybe, but it don't figure.

17:57.625 --> 18:01.500
I've got nothing they want, but they
attack us every time me and you...

18:02.458 --> 18:06.500
Wait a minute. You! They're after you!

18:08.500 --> 18:12.041
Talk, to me, Kit.
What's with you and the pirates?

18:12.125 --> 18:16.667
-Look, what do you care?
-They're shooting up my plane, son!

18:16.750 --> 18:19.500
Yeah, that's all that matters,
your plane, your plane.

18:21.083 --> 18:22.542
Hey, where do you think you're going?

18:24.583 --> 18:28.000
Ah, he'll be back. The birds!

18:29.875 --> 18:34.125
All he cares about is his plane.
I'll get my own plane! Better than his!

18:34.208 --> 18:39.667
Hello, my boy! Long-time no see, <i>si?</i>

18:39.750 --> 18:42.583
Here, birdy, birdy, birdies.

18:42.709 --> 18:44.959
Come to old Baloo.

18:45.041 --> 18:46.291
[sniffing]

18:46.375 --> 18:48.250
[grunting]

18:49.125 --> 18:50.917
Come here, you pillow stuffing!

18:51.000 --> 18:56.208
Still having trouble remembering
where the box is, eh?

18:56.291 --> 19:01.542
Perhaps a night in the jungle will...
jog your memory.

19:02.208 --> 19:06.125
There are numerous hungry animals
in the jungle, you know,

19:06.208 --> 19:07.792
-with sharp, pointy--
-[crunch]

19:07.917 --> 19:09.333
Teeth!

19:09.709 --> 19:12.291
You... You bit me!

19:13.333 --> 19:16.583
March, you overgrown feather dusters.
[chuckles]

19:16.667 --> 19:19.959
Thanks to you, the <i>Sea Duck </i> is all mine!

19:20.500 --> 19:22.667
[Don Karnage]
This is your last chance, boy.

19:22.750 --> 19:24.750
Is the box in the plane?

19:25.709 --> 19:28.709
Plane, what plane? I walked here.

19:28.792 --> 19:32.875
No use protecting your friend.
We will find him.

19:32.959 --> 19:36.208
[scoffs] Friend? I don't have any friends.

19:36.291 --> 19:37.500
It's Kit!

19:37.583 --> 19:38.542
[squawks]

19:38.625 --> 19:40.125
Shh. Quiet.

19:40.125 --> 19:43.583
OK. We'll do it the hard way.

19:43.667 --> 19:49.125
Dumptruck, get me the turnips
and the sandpaper.

19:49.208 --> 19:53.208
That kid's something else.
I got to save him.

19:54.667 --> 19:57.792
Oh, I'm going to hate myself
in the morning.

19:57.875 --> 20:02.041
Excellent. Now, my boy,

20:02.125 --> 20:04.458
I want some answers.

20:04.542 --> 20:09.458
-Stuff it in your windsock!
-My windsock?

20:09.542 --> 20:11.834
Why, you little...

20:12.375 --> 20:13.750
[sniffing]

